Name: Beorn The Bear
Review: We went here as a large group for a friend's birthday celebration. The food was distinctly average, the starters were tolerable and nicely presented but the main courses were entirely bland and unexciting. My friend struggled to finish her steak (which she said was fairly chewy) and the thai green curry I ordered had very little flavour, overly large chunks of chicken and overcooked rice.The table service was rude and the waiter made a number of unwarranted comments towards the female guests, almost every time we went to order something. One friend had to order a simple lemonade twice before it was eventually received. I was also given the wrong drink.Towards the end of the night the floor staff try to shepherd everyone downstairs as they close the upstairs bar and seating areas. Despite us having a table upstairs, we were refused entry to the upstairs bar and the floor manager attempted to push my girlfriend aside whilst she was trying to get back to our table (to collect our coats and say goodbye to our friends). He did not push her but placed his hands on her to stop her moving forward, which was completely unnecessary given we had explained the situation to him. The manager not only refused to apologise for laying his hands upon her, but then suggested we should leave immediately and not be so rude. The whole incident was rather insane and unnecessary and I had to take him aside to explain the situation amd request an apology. Rather than apologise, he rudely walked away, sulking and muttering under his breath.The dancefloor was fine (although extremely sweaty) and the bar staff were all helpful and friendly. I would not eat food here again and don't expect to be treated like a human being. Ironically, the friendliest people there were the bouncers.

Name: Amin Ryu
Review: Absolute rip off. Coke was ¬£5 in 2008.
Owner response: Dear Amin,Thank you for your review, I am deeply sorry a coke was so expensive in 2008.Besides that,  I hope you had a great night and we are looking forward to welcoming you to Wardour in 2022Best Regards

Name: Jamie Spencer
Review: I had reasonable hopes for 100 Wardour Street, as I love German Gymnasium (see my review on here). It was a date night for me and my wife, our son was away, and I had finally accepted I was going to miss the England match‚Ä¶The venue is fairly mad, and I imagine pretty fun if you are young and enjoy mainstream pop of the Sam Smith variety (confession: I do not) but the food‚Ä¶ the food was unforgivably bad.Including a bottle of wine & two g&ts our bill was in excess of ¬£200. Neither of us could eat more than half of our starters or mains.I had squid to start. One of my favourite dishes at German Gymnasium, but this was like some kind of cruel, crude parody. After a few mouthfuls I recalled what the taste reminded me of - Tesco frozen southern friend chicken bites that my mum used to serve up‚Ä¶. A huge portion that largely went undisturbed. My main was monkfish, which again I poked around my plate suspiciously. Rather than the meaty, flavoursome texture I‚Äôm used to I was greeted by a strange, waterlogged, spongy consistency which to be honest slightly turned my stomach. We didn‚Äôt risk a desert. We stumbled out into the streets with empty stomachs and an even emptier wallet, but at least were amused by the sight of the human pyramid that had formed on Eros in Piccadilly Circus.The staff were good and it was so loud in there I saw no point in raising any issues with them, but I did email afterwards to express concerns and got a rather perfunctory reply. That‚Äôs fine - they are a popular venue and don‚Äôt need me to keep them busy. However, I feel honour bound to warn any likeminded food fans to avoid‚Ä¶
Owner response: Dear Jamie, Spencer,Many thanks for the review.I am sorry to hear that your experience to 100 Wardour St. fell below your expectations.Please kindly contact me via the below details so I can look into it.Kind Regards,Anthony B.Deputy General Manageranthonyb@danddlondon.com

The music was horrendous, like the kind of stuff you would hear at a children‚Äôs disco. We were then told to leave because our friend allegedly ‚Äúkicked a glass‚Äù that was already on the floor. This did not happen. They refused to give us a refund for entry (we had only been there for 20 mins). I would literally never return here in a million years. I suggest you save your time and money and go somewhere else.

Review: My dining experience at 14 Hills has been simply unforgettable. In addition, the food was delicious, from starters to mains, from cocktails to wine, everything pleased my palate and made my experience even better. I went to celebrate my 40th birthday with a friend and  I did feel cocooned, spoilt and very special. I was blissfully happy and couldn‚Äôt have started my 40ites in any better way. Thank you so much 14 Hills, I will highly recommend you to everyone I know!

I want to take the opportunity to thank profusely the waiting staff, from the manager Stefano, who has been simply exquisite and went above and beyond with his service, to the waiter Grober, with his infectious smile, and the delightful receptionist, who has been very smiling and kind and offered me a lovely table with a view of the Thames. In addition, the food was delicious, from starters to mains, from cocktails to wine, everything pleased my palate and made my experience even better. I went to celebrate my 40th birthday with a friend and  I did feel cocooned, spoilt and very special. I was blissfully happy and couldn‚Äôt have started my 40ites in any better way. Thank you so much 14 Hills, I will highly recommend you to everyone I know!

Name: moises
Review: Stylish restaurant from the 28-50 chain. Nice deco as usual, the food is usually good and staff great.I like the off white marble tables contrasting with the dark rich velvety purple and brown chairs. Always a nice mix of colours and textures. As always, the lovely little industrial ceiling lights come on their own as it darkens, giving a cosier atmosphere to the place.My only niggle the portions were on the smaller side and it was a tad pricey perhaps but there again you are in South Kensington. Also, I was told they have recently changed the menu, I think it shows, it needs a bit of fine tuning.Having said, the food wasn't bad, just not as good as I would have expected.The bread was good but the butter delicious. Very good taste and texture. I was told it is mixed with yogurt and it shows the creamier and smoother consistency.The crab salad was very tasty, with the mango and avocado pure√© all well balanced.The sole meuniere perhaps the weakest. Small portion  and new potatoes a bit too firm but the fish was well cooked.The chocolate delice dessert very good, the salted caramel ice cream a nice contrast with the chocolate.The staff were great and the service excellent. Special mention to my waiter on the day, Alexander, he was superb!
Owner response: Dear Moises,Thank you for your detailed review.Many thanks for your mention of Alexander, he has recently joined our team and is a great new addition.There are some things you list that may need to be worked on and we will look into these.We hope to see you back with us soon.Kind regards,Ginny

Name: Daniel Chu
Review: I had dinner here for my girlfriend's birthday on the 29/6 and everything was amazing! Very welcoming and helpful towards the menu.The food was great here, a bit pricey but also worth it at the same time. I definitely recommend coming here! Hidden gem that isn't on the main road but very peaceful atmosphere. Great selection from the menu! Had our very first date here and now my girlfriend's birthday. Owner response: Dear Daniel,Thank you for your kind 5-star review and even more so for dining with us again.We hope to see you back with us soon!Kind regards,Ginny

Review: Lovely birthday dinner. This is the third time I've been here and it never disappoints.Service was as always excellent. Our waitress was kind and attentive. She even sang me Happy Birthday. The table next to us sang along and that made the atmosphere even more special. I was truly touched. Thanks to the staff and everyone that made the occasion special.Food was excellent too. Here you always start off with bread and butter on the house, which I think really should be more commonplace at restaurants. I had ratatouille as my main, a traditional French dish which was delicious and nutritious, with a great variety of vegetables. The sweets too were good. The chocolate delice in particular was soft and rather chocolatey without being too sweet. The berry salad was a healthy and naturally delicious dessert for the summer.This place has marked special occasions of mine with such solid service, fantastic food and elegant d√©cor. Well worth recommending.

Name: Martyn Booth
Review: I needed a team dinner event for 11 people recently and this restaurant had space and were very accommodating. The food was okay too (but not excellent).However, they asked for a holding deposit of ¬£110 to secure the booking. Seemed reasonable, so I did it. It was supposed to be knocked off of the bill. When the bill came, it wasn't knocked off. I was told that they rectify these issues afterwards. Suffice to say that they do not. I've emailed the original person I booked with (very responsive before I paid, not responsive at all afterwards), called the restaurant and called the reservation line. Both promised to resolve and call me back and neither did. Very poor behaviour.
Owner response: Hi Martin,You have posted this review on our other restaurants pages as well...We did refund you the deposit the day after your reservation with us.If there is still an issue please get in touch with us (we have tried to call and email you numerous times but you never answer).Kind regards,Ginny

Name: Christopher Simon
Review: This review is about the 28-50 in Draycott Avenue, in Chelsea. Next to Chelsea telephone exchange. Not South Kensington - there is no Draycott Avenue in South Kensington. Never has been. Nor in Knightsbridge. Or Fulham. But there is now another 28-50 in the King's Road, which also happens to be in Chelsea.Anyway, the food here is really good,  and the service is first class. The attention to the wine selection is commendable. Recommended

Name: Nicola Lawrence
Review: Fabulous dinner at this stylish restaurant & wine bar on Draycott Ave. We started with champagne & oysters at the bar, beautifully presented. Richard was charming. Followed by the full "prestige" tasting menu, Barbara helped advise us. Wild mushroom veloute and hanger steak... Perfect. Just spectacular, and the wine background from the sommelier Kesia (?) - a real enthusiast and very inspiring. The service throughout was fabulous and the food amazing. I'll definitely go back!

Name: moises
Review: Stylish restaurant from the 28-50 chain. Nice deco as usual, the food is usually good and staff great.I like the off white marble tables contrasting with the dark rich velvety purple and brown chairs. Always a nice mix of colours and textures. As always, the lovely little industrial ceiling lights come on their own as it darkens, giving a cosier atmosphere to the place.My only niggle the portions were on the smaller side and it was a tad pricey perhaps but there again you are in South Kensington. Also, I was told they have recently changed the menu, I think it shows, it needs a bit of fine tuning.Having said, the food wasn't bad, just not as good as I would have expected.The bread was good but the butter delicious. Very good taste and texture. I was told it is mixed with yogurt and it shows the creamier and smoother consistency.The crab salad was very tasty, with the mango and avocado pure√© all well balanced.The sole meuniere perhaps the weakest. Small portion  and new potatoes a bit too firm but the fish was well cooked.The chocolate delice dessert very good, the salted caramel ice cream a nice contrast with the chocolate.The staff were great and the service excellent. Special mention to my waiter on the day, Alexander, he was superb!
Owner response: Dear Moises,Thank you for your detailed review.Many thanks for your mention of Alexander, he has recently joined our team and is a great new addition.There are some things you list that may need to be worked on and we will look into these.We hope to see you back with us soon.Kind regards,Ginny

Name: Daniel Chu
Review: I had dinner here for my girlfriend's birthday on the 29/6 and everything was amazing! Service from Aleksandr and the woman waitress (I didn't get your name but you know who you are, the one who sung happy birthday) were outstanding! Very welcoming and helpful towards the menu.The food was great here, a bit pricey but also worth it at the same time. I definitely recommend coming here! Hidden gem that isn't on the main road but very peaceful atmosphere. Great selection from the menu! Had our very first date here and now my girlfriend's birthday. Will be coming again for another special occasion.Thank you to everyone there for making it special!
Owner response: Dear Daniel,Thank you for your kind 5-star review and even more so for dining with us again.We hope to see you back with us soon!Kind regards,Ginny

Name: Gabrielle Lee
Review: Lovely birthday dinner. This is the third time I've been here and it never disappoints.Service was as always excellent. Our waitress was kind and attentive. She even sang me Happy Birthday. The table next to us sang along and that made the atmosphere even more special. I was truly touched. Thanks to the staff and everyone that made the occasion special.Food was excellent too. Here you always start off with bread and butter on the house, which I think really should be more commonplace at restaurants. I had ratatouille as my main, a traditional French dish which was delicious and nutritious, with a great variety of vegetables. The sweets too were good. The chocolate delice in particular was soft and rather chocolatey without being too sweet. The berry salad was a healthy and naturally delicious dessert for the summer.This place has marked special occasions of mine with such solid service, fantastic food and elegant d√©cor. Well worth recommending.

Name: Martyn Booth
Review: I needed a team dinner event for 11 people recently and this restaurant had space and were very accommodating. The food was okay too (but not excellent).However, they asked for a holding deposit of ¬£110 to secure the booking. Seemed reasonable, so I did it. It was supposed to be knocked off of the bill. When the bill came, it wasn't knocked off. I was told that they rectify these issues afterwards. Suffice to say that they do not. I've emailed the original person I booked with (very responsive before I paid, not responsive at all afterwards), called the restaurant and called the reservation line. Both promised to resolve and call me back and neither did. Very poor behaviour.
Owner response: Hi Martin,You have posted this review on our other restaurants pages as well...We did refund you the deposit the day after your reservation with us.If there is still an issue please get in touch with us (we have tried to call and email you numerous times but you never answer).Kind regards,Ginny

Name: Christopher Simon
Review: This review is about the 28-50 in Draycott Avenue, in Chelsea. Next to Chelsea telephone exchange. Not South Kensington - there is no Draycott Avenue in South Kensington. Never has been. Nor in Knightsbridge. Or Fulham. But there is now another 28-50 in the King's Road, which also happens to be in Chelsea.Anyway, the food here is really good,  and the service is first class. The attention to the wine selection is commendable. Recommended

Name: Nicola Lawrence
Review: Fabulous dinner at this stylish restaurant & wine bar on Draycott Ave. We started with champagne & oysters at the bar, beautifully presented. Richard was charming. Followed by the full "prestige" tasting menu, Barbara helped advise us. Wild mushroom veloute and hanger steak... Perfect. Just spectacular, and the wine background from the sommelier Kesia (?) - a real enthusiast and very inspiring. The service throughout was fabulous and the food amazing. I'll definitely go back!

Name: moises
Review: Stylish restaurant from the 28-50 chain. Nice deco as usual, the food is usually good and staff great.I like the off white marble tables contrasting with the dark rich velvety purple and brown chairs. Always a nice mix of colours and textures. As always, the lovely little industrial ceiling lights come on their own as it darkens, giving a cosier atmosphere to the place.My only niggle the portions were on the smaller side and it was a tad pricey perhaps but there again you are in South Kensington. Also, I was told they have recently changed the menu, I think it shows, it needs a bit of fine tuning.Having said, the food wasn't bad, just not as good as I would have expected.The bread was good but the butter delicious. Very good taste and texture. I was told it is mixed with yogurt and it shows the creamier and smoother consistency.The crab salad was very tasty, with the mango and avocado pure√© all well balanced.The sole meuniere perhaps the weakest. Small portion  and new potatoes a bit too firm but the fish was well cooked.The chocolate delice dessert very good, the salted caramel ice cream a nice contrast with the chocolate.The staff were great and the service excellent. Special mention to my waiter on the day, Alexander, he was superb!
Owner response: Dear Moises,Thank you for your detailed review.Many thanks for your mention of Alexander, he has recently joined our team and is a great new addition.There are some things you list that may need to be worked on and we will look into these.We hope to see you back with us soon.Kind regards,Ginny

Name: Daniel Chu
Review: I had dinner here for my girlfriend's birthday on the 29/6 and everything was amazing! Service from Aleksandr and the woman waitress (I didn't get your name but you know who you are, the one who sung happy birthday) were outstanding! Very welcoming and helpful towards the menu.The food was great here, a bit pricey but also worth it at the same time. I definitely recommend coming here! Hidden gem that isn't on the main road but very peaceful atmosphere. Great selection from the menu! Had our very first date here and now my girlfriend's birthday. Will be coming again for another special occasion.Thank you to everyone there for making it special!
Owner response: Dear Daniel,Thank you for your kind 5-star review and even more so for dining with us again.We hope to see you back with us soon!Kind regards,Ginny

Name: Gabrielle Lee
Review: Lovely birthday dinner. This is the third time I've been here and it never disappoints.Service was as always excellent. Our waitress was kind and attentive. She even sang me Happy Birthday. The table next to us sang along and that made the atmosphere even more special. I was truly touched. Thanks to the staff and everyone that made the occasion special.Food was excellent too. Here you always start off with bread and butter on the house, which I think really should be more commonplace at restaurants. I had ratatouille as my main, a traditional French dish which was delicious and nutritious, with a great variety of vegetables. The sweets too were good. The chocolate delice in particular was soft and rather chocolatey without being too sweet. The berry salad was a healthy and naturally delicious dessert for the summer.This place has marked special occasions of mine with such solid service, fantastic food and elegant d√©cor. Well worth recommending.

Name: Lukas Georgiou
Review: We booked a table at 28-50 Chelsea for mother's day. They double booked, and moved us with less than 48 hours notice to Kensington, so we had to adjust our plans a bit. We were told that the group would receive "free bubbles on arrival and free desserts" as compensation for the change.At the Kensington branch, the food was impeccable and the service was great. However there was no mention of us being moved or the compensation offered. Instead the server offered a "free gift" of sparkling wine "to the ladies but unfortunately not the men". This was an archaic and offensive statement considering I am a non-binary person. Two out of five people at the table got the compensatory drinks.  We were also made to pay for our desserts. I'm sure it was just a miscommunication between the branches but kind of a weird slip-up that left me with a bad taste.But as I said, the food was great.
Owner response: Dear Lukas,Plainly, I am very sorry about the miscommunication and that the complimentary desserts and Champagne were not offered.Please get in touch with me (Ginny) directly via call and we will make it up to you.Kind regards,Ginny

Here you always start off with bread and butter on the house, which I think really should be more commonplace at restaurants. I had ratatouille as my main, a traditional French dish which was delicious and nutritious, with a great variety of vegetables. The sweets too were good. The chocolate delice in particular was soft and rather chocolatey without being too sweet. The berry salad was a healthy and naturally delicious dessert for the summer.This place has marked special occasions of mine with such solid service, fantastic food and elegant d√©cor. Well worth recommending.

Name: Nicola Lawrence
Review: Fabulous dinner at this stylish restaurant & wine bar on Draycott Ave. We started with champagne & oysters at the bar, beautifully presented. Richard was charming. Followed by the full "prestige" tasting menu, Barbara helped advise us. Wild mushroom veloute and hanger steak... Perfect. Just spectacular, and the wine background from the sommelier Kesia (?) - a real enthusiast and very inspiring. The service throughout was fabulous and the food amazing. I'll definitely go back!

Name: moises
Review: Stylish restaurant from the 28-50 chain. Nice deco as usual, the food is usually good and staff great.I like the off white marble tables contrasting with the dark rich velvety purple and brown chairs. Always a nice mix of colours and textures. As always, the lovely little industrial ceiling lights come on their own as it darkens, giving a cosier atmosphere to the place.My only niggle the portions were on the smaller side and it was a tad pricey perhaps but there again you are in South Kensington. Also, I was told they have recently changed the menu, I think it shows, it needs a bit of fine tuning.Having said, the food wasn't bad, just not as good as I would have expected.The bread was good but the butter delicious. Very good taste and texture. I was told it is mixed with yogurt and it shows the creamier and smoother consistency.The crab salad was very tasty, with the mango and avocado pure√© all well balanced.The sole meuniere perhaps the weakest. Small portion  and new potatoes a bit too firm but the fish was well cooked.The chocolate delice dessert very good, the salted caramel ice cream a nice contrast with the chocolate.The staff were great and the service excellent. Special mention to my waiter on the day, Alexander, he was superb!
Owner response: Dear Moises,Thank you for your detailed review.Many thanks for your mention of Alexander, he has recently joined our team and is a great new addition.There are some things you list that may need to be worked on and we will look into these.We hope to see you back with us soon.Kind regards,Ginny

Name: Martyn Booth
Review: I needed a team dinner event for 11 people recently and this restaurant had space and were very accommodating. The food was okay too (but not excellent).However, they asked for a holding deposit of ¬£110 to secure the booking. Seemed reasonable, so I did it. It was supposed to be knocked off of the bill. When the bill came, it wasn't knocked off. I was told that they rectify these issues afterwards. Suffice to say that they do not. I've emailed the original person I booked with (very responsive before I paid, not responsive at all afterwards), called the restaurant and called the reservation line. Both promised to resolve and call me back and neither did. Very poor behaviour.
Owner response: Hi Martin,You have posted this review on our other restaurants pages as well...We did refund you the deposit the day after your reservation with us.If there is still an issue please get in touch with us (we have tried to call and email you numerous times but you never answer).Kind regards,Ginny

Name: Christopher Simon
Review: This review is about the 28-50 in Draycott Avenue, in Chelsea. Next to Chelsea telephone exchange. Not South Kensington - there is no Draycott Avenue in South Kensington. Never has been. Nor in Knightsbridge. Or Fulham. But there is now another 28-50 in the King's Road, which also happens to be in Chelsea.Anyway, the food here is really good,  and the service is first class. The attention to the wine selection is commendable. Recommended

Name: Nicola Lawrence
Review: Fabulous dinner at this stylish restaurant & wine bar on Draycott Ave. We started with champagne & oysters at the bar, beautifully presented. Richard was charming. Followed by the full "prestige" tasting menu, Barbara helped advise us. Wild mushroom veloute and hanger steak... Perfect. Just spectacular, and the wine background from the sommelier Kesia (?) - a real enthusiast and very inspiring. The service throughout was fabulous and the food amazing. I'll definitely go back!

Vendor Name: All Bar One New Oxford Street
Place: All Bar One New Oxford Street
Name: moises
Review: Stylish restaurant from the 28-50 chain. Nice deco as usual, the food is usually good and staff great.I like the off white marble tables contrasting with the dark rich velvety purple and brown chairs. Always a nice mix of colours and textures. As always, the lovely little industrial ceiling lights come on their own as it darkens, giving a cosier atmosphere to the place.My only niggle the portions were on the smaller side and it was a tad pricey perhaps but there again you are in South Kensington. Also, I was told they have recently changed the menu, I think it shows, it needs a bit of fine tuning.Having said, the food wasn't bad, just not as good as I would have expected.The bread was good but the butter delicious. Very good taste and texture. I was told it is mixed with yogurt and it shows the creamier and smoother consistency.The crab salad was very tasty, with the mango and avocado pure√© all well balanced.The sole meuniere perhaps the weakest. Small portion  and new potatoes a bit too firm but the fish was well cooked.The chocolate delice dessert very good, the salted caramel ice cream a nice contrast with the chocolate.The staff were great and the service excellent. Special mention to my waiter on the day, Alexander, he was superb!
Owner response: Dear Moises,Thank you for your detailed review.Many thanks for your mention of Alexander, he has recently joined our team and is a great new addition.There are some things you list that may need to be worked on and we will look into these.We hope to see you back with us soon.Kind regards,Ginny

Vendor Name: All Bar One New Oxford Street
Place: All Bar One New Oxford Street
Name: Daniel Chu
Review: I had dinner here for my girlfriend's birthday on the 29/6 and everything was amazing! Service from Aleksandr and the woman waitress (I didn't get your name but you know who you are, the one who sung happy birthday) were outstanding! Very welcoming and helpful towards the menu.The food was great here, a bit pricey but also worth it at the same time. I definitely recommend coming here! Hidden gem that isn't on the main road but very peaceful atmosphere. Great selection from the menu! Had our very first date here and now my girlfriend's birthday. Will be coming again for another special occasion.Thank you to everyone there for making it special!
Owner response: Dear Daniel,Thank you for your kind 5-star review and even more so for dining with us again.We hope to see you back with us soon!Kind regards,Ginny

Vendor Name: All Bar One New Oxford Street
Place: All Bar One New Oxford Street
Name: Gabrielle Lee
Review: Lovely birthday dinner. This is the third time I've been here and it never disappoints.Service was as always excellent. Our waitress was kind and attentive. She even sang me Happy Birthday. The table next to us sang along and that made the atmosphere even more special. I was truly touched. Thanks to the staff and everyone that made the occasion special.Food was excellent too. Here you always start off with bread and butter on the house, which I think really should be more commonplace at restaurants. I had ratatouille as my main, a traditional French dish which was delicious and nutritious, with a great variety of vegetables. The sweets too were good. The chocolate delice in particular was soft and rather chocolatey without being too sweet. The berry salad was a healthy and naturally delicious dessert for the summer.This place has marked special occasions of mine with such solid service, fantastic food and elegant d√©cor. Well worth recommending.

Vendor Name: All Bar One New Oxford Street
Place: All Bar One New Oxford Street
Name: Lukas Georgiou
Review: We booked a table at 28-50 Chelsea for mother's day. They double booked, and moved us with less than 48 hours notice to Kensington, so we had to adjust our plans a bit. We were told that the group would receive "free bubbles on arrival and free desserts" as compensation for the change.At the Kensington branch, the food was impeccable and the service was great. However there was no mention of us being moved or the compensation offered. Instead the server offered a "free gift" of sparkling wine "to the ladies but unfortunately not the men". This was an archaic and offensive statement considering I am a non-binary person. Two out of five people at the table got the compensatory drinks.  We were also made to pay for our desserts. I'm sure it was just a miscommunication between the branches but kind of a weird slip-up that left me with a bad taste.But as I said, the food was great.
Owner response: Dear Lukas,Plainly, I am very sorry about the miscommunication and that the complimentary desserts and Champagne were not offered.Please get in touch with me (Ginny) directly via call and we will make it up to you.Kind regards,Ginny
